Consider the function

\begin{align*}
f(x) = x^2e^{-x}
\end{align*}

defined on the whole real line.

Find all zeros of $\displaystyle f, f'$ and $\displaystyle f''$ and
determine all local minima, maxima and inflection points of \emph{f}.
Sketch the graph of \emph{f}. You may use the fact that
$\lim_{x \to \infty} x^2 e^{-x} = 0$.
